    "unique_note": "Uniquely, THIS TEMPLE IS NAMED AFTER THE THAYAR (Nachiyar) rather than the Perumal — a distinct rarity in Divya Desams. Sri Vanchulavalli Thayar holds EQUAL sovereignty with Vishnu here, expressing the Sri Vaishnava theological ideal of Lakshmi-Narayana as inseparable divine couple. Famous for its GARUDA VAHANA (stone Garuda vehicle) — during festival processions, the Utsavar mounted on the stone Garuda mysteriously grows heavier at each ritual stop, requiring more devotees to carry — an unexplained phenomenon that has continued for centuries.",
